<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<h2 id="head-3a7f70bda73a2c13b658790601da132fdf11efda"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Fate</h2>
Numerous spirits inhabit the land of Arda, from the murderous barrow wights to the enigmatic Tom Bombadil. These spirits usually are bound to a specific geographic region, but there are exceptions to this rule. Sometimes one of these spirits will anonymously take interest in an adventurer. This can either be very, very good or very, very bad. These spirits will "rig" reality to ensure that something happens -- or doesn't happen. <p>
If you acquire a fate, a message will pop up briefly on your screen to inform you of the event, but this message will not tell you what that fate is. To discover this, you must: 
</p>

    <ol type="1">

    <li>
<p>
Visit a Soothsayer. He or she will uncover the fate, but not tell you what it is. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
Use the key combinations 'shift' + '`' (~) to display current knowledge. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
Type '9' to display your currently identified fates. 
</p>
</li>

    </ol>


<h2 id="head-8a45d339a638ac247a1574d733c588c338c1cb6e"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Credit</h2>
The help on fates was originally written for PernAngband 5.x.x by Dustin Ragan, who has graciously granted his permission for us to use and update that text here. </div><div id="footer">


